When we got there, he took the chalk and drew several heavy lines across the bottom of the driveway.&nbsp; As I watched, I saw ants divert from their path and head away from the house.&nbsp; They would not cross that chalk line.&nbsp; Uncle Hiram was right!&nbsp; Ants can be controlled by drawing a chalk line!&nbsp; <span class=\"marker\">As Edgar Smith (2012) explains in his book, <em>Pesky Pests</em>,</span> &quot;When ants are on the move, they create a pheromone trail for other ants to follow. Drawing the chalk line breaks up the pheromones, dispersing the army of ants from their march&quot; <span class=\"marker\">(p. 21)</span>.</span></td></tr></tbody></table>"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":1,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"audioPath":"7"},"leftText":"<table cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"ju-powertip\" style=\"width:90%;\"><thead><tr><th scope=\"col\"><strong>Careful!</strong></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><p>Sometimes, you may read information that states an idea that is the same as your own idea.&nbsp; Use direct quotations in your writing to support your own ideas.&nbsp; Use a direct quotation when it is important that your reader views the exact words from the source.<br /><br />In your family history, you are writing about a relative who was one of the first riders for the Pony Express.&nbsp; You add a direct quotation about the age of Pony Express riders.<br /><br />To give credit, you include a citation after the quotation.<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p><span class=\"ju-labels\" style=\"color:#59595B;font-family:tahoma;font-weight:bold;\">From your family history:</span></p><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"ju-tableplain\"><tbody><tr><td><span class=\"ju-double-space\" style=\"color:#552656;font-family:lato,sans-serif;font-size:15px;line-height:180%;\">Some of you have heard the stories of Uncle Frank Webner, who was one of the first riders for the Pony Express in the 1860s.&nbsp; Frank would ride from Missouri to California delivering mail in approximately 10 days.&nbsp; He began his career at the age of 14.&nbsp; To us, it may seem amazing to think of a middle school-aged person taking on such a solitary and dangerous job, but, in fact, this was very common. &quot;It wasn&#39;t unusual for teenagers as young as 14 to be hired. One rider named &#39;Bronco&#39; Charlie Miller claimed he was only 11 years old when he first joined the&nbsp;Pony Express&quot;<span class=\"marker\"> (Andrews, 2016, p. 21).</span></span></td></tr></tbody></table>","headerText":"Direct quotations"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":1,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"audioPath":"11"},"leftText":"<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"ju-powertip\" style=\"width:90%;\"><thead><tr><th scope=\"col\">DID YOU KNOW?&nbsp; Instead, start a new paragraph indenting the entire quotation by one-half inch.&nbsp;</li></ul><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/picture_it.png\" /> <a href=\"S3_BUCKET_/JCS100/2/Pictureit_Directquotation.pdf\" onclick=\"window.open(this.href, '', 'resizable=yes,status=no,location=no,toolbar=no,menubar=no,fullscreen=no,scrollbars=no,dependent=yes,width=826,left=100,height=750,top=50'); loads as light as possible.</td></tr><tr><td><span class=\"ju-labels\" style=\"color:#59595B;font-family:tahoma;font-weight:bold;\">Paraphrase:</span></td><td>To reduce the weight carried by the Pony Express horses, the Pony Express management sought slender or undersized riders.</td></tr></tbody></table>","headerText":"Paraphrasing a source"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"audioPath":"13"},"leftText":"<p>In your family history, you want to let the family know how colorful Uncle Frank&#39;s job was.&nbsp; You have found a source with some fascinating information about the Pony Express.<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p><span class=\"ju-labels\" style=\"color:#59595B;font-family:tahoma;font-weight:bold;\">Original source material:</span></p><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"ju-tableplain\" style=\"color:black;font-family:times new roman,serif;font-size:14px;width:100%;\"><tbody><tr><td>In the mid-19th century, California-bound mail had to be taken either overland by a 25-day stagecoach or spend months inside a ship during a long sea voyage. The Pony Express, meanwhile, had an average delivery time of only10 days. To achieve this remarkable speed, company owners William H. Russell, William B. Waddell, and Alexander Majors set up a string of nearly 200 relief stations across what is now Missouri, Kansas, Nebraska, Colorado, Wyoming, Utah, Nevada, and California. Lone horsemen would ride between stations at a breakneck pace, switching mounts every 10 to 15 miles and then handing their cargo to a new courier after 75 to 200 miles. The relay system allowed mail to crisscross the frontier in record time. &nbsp;In March, 1861 Abraham Lincoln&#39;s first inaugural address was delivered from Nebraska to California in just 7 days by proud riders for the Pony Express.</td></tr></tbody></table>"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"audioPath":"14"},"leftText":"<p>You want to give your family as many details as possible to paint a colorful picture of Uncle Frank&#39;s life, so you <strong>paraphrase</strong> the information from the source, including all the ideas and details.&nbsp;<br /><br />To give credit, you include a citation at the end of the paraphrase.<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p><span class=\"ju-labels\" style=\"color:#59595B;font-family:tahoma;font-weight:bold;\">Paraphrase from your family history:</span></p><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"ju-tableplain\" style=\"width:100%;\"><tbody><tr><td><span class=\"ju-double-space\" style=\"color:#552656;font-family:lato,sans-serif;font-size:15px;line-height:180%;\">Americans living in the mid-1800s and wishing to send mail to California had to choose between sending their communications via a 25-day stagecoach ride or via ship, which could take several months.&nbsp; The Pony Express, begun by William H. Russell, William B. Waddell, and Alexander Majors, offered the innovative and fast option of delivering mail to California in 10 days.&nbsp; Riders rode between stations placed across what is now Missouri, Kansas, Nebraska, Colorado, Wyoming, Utah, Nevada, and California, handing the mail to new riders after 75 to 200 miles.&nbsp; The Pony Express relay system enabled the company to achieve an important milestone in 1861 when riders carried a copy of Abraham Lincoln&rsquo;s inaugural address from Nebraska to California in one week <span class=\"marker\">(Andrews, 2016)</span>.&nbsp;</span></td></tr></tbody></table>"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":1,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"audioPath":"15"},"leftText":"<table cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"ju-powertip\" style=\"width:90%;\"><thead><tr><th scope=\"col\">DID YOU KNOW?&nbsp; Paraphrasing<span class=\"screen-reader-only\" style=\"background-color:#FA839F;\">&nbsp;,</span></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><ul style=\"padding-left: 15px;\"><li>Read the passage and make sure you understand everything being said.<br />&nbsp;</li><li>Explain all the details of the passage in your own words and with a different sentence structure.&nbsp; You may use important or technical key terms from the original passage.<br />&nbsp;</li><li>Generally, a paraphrase will be similar in length to the original passage, since you are keeping the same main ideas and details.<br />&nbsp;</li><li>Do NOT include quotation marks.<br />&nbsp;</li><li>Include a citation.</li></ul><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/picture_it.png\" /> <a href=\"S3_BUCKET_/JCS100/2/Pictureit_Paraphrasing.pdf\" onclick=\"window.open(this.href, '', 'resizable=yes,status=no,location=no,toolbar=no,menubar=no,fullscreen=no,scrollbars=no,dependent=yes,width=826,left=100,height=750,top=50'); When you paraphrase, do not borrow too many words from the original source or repeat the sentence structures.<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p><span class=\"ju-labels\" style=\"color:#59595B;font-family:tahoma;font-weight:bold;\">Original source material:</span></p><p>The Pony Express specifically recruited riders who were small, thus keeping the horses&#39; loads as light as possible.<br /><br /><span class=\"ju-orangetimesph\" style=\"color:#F79A1F;font-weight:bold;\">x</span> <span class=\"ju-labels\" style=\"color:#59595B;font-family:tahoma;font-weight:bold;\">Unacceptable paraphrase:</span></p><p>The Pony Express deliberately hired riders of small stature, ensuring that horses&#39; burdens were not very heavy.<br /><br /><span class=\"ju-greencheckph\" style=\"color:#08A47D;font-weight:bold;\">v</span> <span class=\"ju-labels\" style=\"color:#59595B;font-family:tahoma;font-weight:bold;\">Acceptable paraphrase:</span></p><p>To reduce the weight carried by the Pony Express horses, the Pony Express management sought slender or undersized riders.</p>"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"audioPath":"17"},"leftText":"<p>Can you tell why the paraphrase is not acceptable? &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /><br />It uses<strong> </strong>the same structure and most of the same words as the original source.&nbsp; The writer has changed only a word or two in each sentence.<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p><span class=\"ju-labels\" style=\"color:#59595B;font-family:tahoma;font-weight:bold;\">Original source material:</span></p><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"ju-tableplain\" style=\"color:black;font-family:times new roman,serif;font-size:14px;width:100%;\"><tbody><tr><td>The speed of the Pony Express didn&rsquo;t come cheap.&nbsp; In its early days the service cost $5 for every half-ounce of mail&mdash;the equivalent of some $130 today.&nbsp; Prices were later reduced to just $1, but they remained too high for everyday mail. &nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span class=\"ju-orangetimesph\" style=\"color:#F79A1F;font-weight:bold;\">x</span> <span class=\"ju-labels\" style=\"color:#59595B;font-family:tahoma;font-weight:bold;\">Unacceptable paraphrase:</span></p><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"ju-tableplain\" style=\"width: 100%;\"><tbody><tr><td><span class=\"ju-double-space\" style=\"color:#552656;font-family:lato,sans-serif;font-size:15px;line-height:180%;\">The speed of the Pony Express was not inexpensive.&nbsp; In its early days the service cost $5 for every half-ounce of mail&mdash;the equivalent of some $130 today.&nbsp; Prices were later dropped to just $1, but they remained too high for ordinary mail. (Andrews, 2016).</span></td></tr></tbody></table>"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":1,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"audioPath":"18"},"leftText":"<p>When you use the main ideas from an original source and use your own words to explain what you mean, you are <strong>summarizing.</strong><br /><br />When you write or create a presentation, you may summarize long passages or large amounts of information.<br /><br />In your summary, you will include the main ideas from the original source, but none of the details. Your summary will be considerably shorter than the original.&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p><span class=\"ju-labels\" style=\"color:#59595B;font-family:tahoma;font-weight:bold;\">Original source material:</span></p><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"ju-tableplain\" style=\"color: black; font-family: times new roman,serif; font-size: 14px; width: 100%;\"><tbody><tr><td>During the 1930s, Coney Island in New York City was a haven for city folks who wanted to escape the oppressive summer heat. New Yorkers flocked to the beach to cool off in the waves and socialize with friends and family.
